      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Week 3 of "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "Summer into AI 2026"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " hosted by "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "@advisoryhour"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " — theme: Data.Punk."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Every 60 seconds, a rotating globe comes alive with real earthquake data — every M2.5+ tremor from today plotted at its exact coordinates, color-coded by magnitude. Claude watches the seismic, market, and atmospheric feeds together and delivers a live planetary briefing in documentary voice. This is what government data looks like when you actually build something with it."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Worth noting alongside this: "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "other Data.Punk entries"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " focused on dashboards and dataset explorers — this one synthesizes three live feeds into a cinematic monitoring station with a voiced AI narrator"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How the AI works"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Live data pipeline"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — Three public APIs run in parallel every cycle: USGS earthquake feed (M2.5+ events, last 24 hours), CoinGecko crypto prices, and Open-Meteo weather for 5 cities. No API keys required."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Claude streaming briefing"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — All three feeds are handed to claude-sonnet-4-6 which streams a 4–5 sentence planetary status report in real time, nature documentary style. The text types itself onto the screen as Claude thinks."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "ElevenLabs voice narration"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — Once the briefing is complete, the full text is sent to ElevenLabs (Rachel voice) and plays back automatically — turning the data into a live broadcast you hear, not just read."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Orthographic globe with D3-geo"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — Every earthquake is projected at its exact lat/lon on a rotating globe built with D3's geoOrthographic projection. Hover any dot to see the USGS place name and depth. M5+ events get permanent labels with leader lines."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How to play"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Open the demo — the globe starts spinning immediately, loading real country borders from Natural Earth 110m data"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Watch the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "earthquake dots"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " appear: green = M2.5, yellow = M3, orange = M4, red = M5, crimson = M6+. Pulsing rings mark the big ones."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Hover any dot to see the exact USGS location name and depth in km"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Click anywhere to unlock audio, then wait for the 60-second cycle — Claude's briefing streams in, then "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "ElevenLabs narrates it aloud"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
